Guidelines in psychiatry
guidelines are important to the effective implementation of modern psychiatry. review Article, using various sources. the writer's own experience of drafting guidelines is drawn upon, while pubmed articles have been searched on how to implement guidelines. the utility of guidelines are discussed and the relationship of guidelines to audit is explained. guidelines need to be effectively researched in order to have credibility; they need to be properly implemented in order to achieve desired improvement in practice and their implementation needs to be audited. 